Key Match Events: Jhoan Duran surrendered four runs in the 10th inning, leading to an 8-6 victory for the Atlanta Braves in extra innings.
Pierce Johnson struck out Matt Wallner to end the contest and send the Twins to their seventh loss in nine games.
Marcell Ozuna started the four-run outburst with a double off the glove of Austin Martin in center.
Travis d’Arnaud followed with an RBI single before Ramón Laureano broke the game wide open with a two-run double off Duran.
José Miranda and Trevor Larnach singled in runs in the bottom of the 10th to get the Twins within two runs.
Trailing 4-0 in the seventh inning, the Twins scored three times as Larnach and Julien each doubled in runs with a Wallner RBI single sandwiched in between.
Larnach’s two-out RBI single off Braves closer Raisel Iglesias tied the score at 4.
Post-Match Reflections: Ryan Jeffers expressed frustration over the loss, emphasizing the importance of every game as the season comes to an end.
Rocco Baldelli highlighted the need for players to step into roles and play complete baseball games.
